::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:09.950 --> 00:00:11.160
What a shame!

3
00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:13.370
I win again!

4
00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:16.500
You guys have a lot of free time.

5
00:00:16.870 --> 00:00:18.870
Hand over the cell keys.

6
00:00:18.870 --> 00:00:20.040
Huh?

7
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:23.380
Who the hell are you?

8
00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:28.720
Hey.

9
00:00:39.980 --> 00:00:43.020
Who said you imbeciles could speak?

10
00:00:42.860 --> 00:00:45.070
<b>"Ghost Princess" Perona
Hollow-Hollow Fruit</b>

11
00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:47.030
What'd you say?!

12
00:00:47.030 --> 00:00:49.900
You've got some nerve, missy.

13
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:55.080
Maybe a simple "Shut up"
is easier to understand?

14
00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:02.920
Kneel before me.

15
00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:05.090
Negative...

16
00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:06.340
Hollow!

17
00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:12.590
Negative! Negative!

18
00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:24.980
I'm sorry that I'm more cowardly
than a water flea...

19
00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:28.570
I wanna give up piracy
and live out my days in prison...

20
00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:38.120
Alright, we're set!

21
00:01:38.120 --> 00:01:40.000
Let's go, guys.

22
00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:02.190
Not very lively around here...

23
00:02:06.020 --> 00:02:07.400
Hey! You!

24
00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:08.520
Huh?

25
00:02:19.370 --> 00:02:22.120
Ouch. Ow, ow, ow...

26
00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:23.500
Hey, you.

27
00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:24.670
Huh?

28
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:31.340
You're...

29
00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:37.300
Are you the one they call Koby the Hero?!

30
00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:39.260
<b>Captain Koby
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>

31
00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:45.560
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

32
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:47.520
Moria?

33
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.450
Gecko Moria is here?

34
00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:57.200
Yes, he is!

35
00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:59.660
Master Moria's life is at risk!

36
00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.290
Free him...?

37
00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:10.420
US, US

38
00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:16.280
US, ALL OF US

39
00:03:19.910 --> 00:03:22.710
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

40
00:03:22.710 --> 00:03:25.470
We all have different places we want to go

41
00:03:23.310 --> 00:03:24.690
We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

42
00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:28.250
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

43
00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:32.600
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

44
00:03:33.870 --> 00:03:36.190
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

45
00:03:36.190 --> 00:03:37.470
ONE PIECE!!

46
00:03:37.830 --> 00:03:40.450
ALL OF US, I've got a question for you
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

47
00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:44.040
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

48
00:03:45.680 --> 00:03:52.240
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

49
00:03:52.350 --> 00:03:58.970
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

50
00:03:58.970 --> 00:04:01.560
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

51
00:04:00.560 --> 00:04:02.090
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

52
00:04:01.620 --> 00:04:05.140
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

53
00:04:06.830 --> 00:04:09.520
Random clues suddenly fit together

54
00:04:09.520 --> 00:04:13.450
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

55
00:04:13.450 --> 00:04:19.920
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

56
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:25.620
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

57
00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:28.190
US, US

58
00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:33.300
US, ALL OF US

59
00:04:37.050 --> 00:04:41.430
<b>The Legendary Hero</b>

60
00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:43.220
Big news!

61
00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:47.100
<b>Beehive, the Pirate Island
New World</b>

62
00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:45.890
Captain Koby has escaped!

63
00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:47.100
Seriously?!

64
00:04:49.810 --> 00:04:52.940
He escaped, so he's not
the commodore's prize anymore, right?!

65
00:04:52.940 --> 00:04:55.530
How much will we get if we capture him?!

66
00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:00.990
Well, we don't need to put a bounty on him!

67
00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:03.490
Cross Guild will pay it for us!

68
00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:06.370
I bought odds on him with a win ticket!

69
00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:08.330
The payout's gonna be big!

70
00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:10.330
How much will we get if we kill him?!

71
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:12.630
Wait till you hear this!

72
00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:16.750
He's a five-star bounty!

73
00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:20.420
That means five treasure chests!
A total of 500 million berries!

74
00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:23.050
A five-star bounty?!

75
00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:25.260
Captains are usually only worth one!

76
00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:31.100
Alright! Let's hit the jackpot!

77
00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.980
Let the hunt begin!

78
00:05:36.270 --> 00:05:39.320
I'm feeline a tickle on
the left side of my chest.

79
00:05:39.650 --> 00:05:42.950
That's where the slaves are
held before they're sold...

80
00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:51.250
Are they breaking out?!

81
00:05:51.580 --> 00:05:53.750
The slaves escaped?!

82
00:05:54.580 --> 00:05:56.960
Can we hunt them, Pizarro?!

83
00:05:56.960 --> 00:05:58.590
Don't be stupid!

84
00:05:58.590 --> 00:06:00.420
You guys are so greedy!

85
00:06:00.970 --> 00:06:02.680
Bring them all back!

86
00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:04.140
Don't even kill Koby...

87
00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:06.220
or I'll tell Teach!

88
00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:11.020
Why is that mountain talking...?

89
00:06:11.390 --> 00:06:13.520
He knows that we're here!

90
00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:14.730
Let's hurry!

91
00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:18.690
What?

92
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.650
This is it for us...

93
00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:26.660
Just run away before we slow you down.

94
00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:28.870
Don't give up hope.

95
00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:31.250
I'll lure them all away...

96
00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:35.880
so make sure everyone escapes!

97
00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:36.630
Well then...

98
00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:39.210
We'll meet again!

99
00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:42.760
Thanks!

100
00:06:45.010 --> 00:06:47.220
Thank you, Captain Koby...

101
00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.600
You're a saint!

102
00:06:57.560 --> 00:07:00.480
<b>Shiryu of the Rain
Clear-Clear Fruit
Invisible Man</b>

103
00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:05.070
You should have captured
them yourself, Pizarro.

104
00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:12.410
Like I said, Teach would be pissed.

105
00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:15.410
<b>"Corrupt King" Avalo Pizarro
Isle-Isle Fruit
Island Man</b>

106
00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:19.040
I just break things whenever I meowve.

107
00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:19.880
Huh?

108
00:07:23.260 --> 00:07:25.800
Mind if I take a shot?

109
00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:29.010
Vasco Shot... What are mew gonna do?

110
00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:38.980
They can't run if I burn down the town.

111
00:07:38.520 --> 00:07:42.070
<b>"Heavy Drinker" Vasco Shot
Glug-Glug Fruit
Booze Man</b>

112
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:52.990
Hey, don't do that!
That would be a meowssive fire!

113
00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:55.450
Teach would be furrious!

114
00:07:55.450 --> 00:07:58.210
It's fine. Leave it to me.

115
00:07:58.710 --> 00:08:03.300
Furget it! We just finished
fixing up Rocky Port!

116
00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:07.170
Would you rather leave it to Wolf?

117
00:08:11.430 --> 00:08:12.760
Wolf?

118
00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:16.980
<b>"Colossal Battleship" Sanjuan Wolf
Huge-Huge Fruit
Gigantification Man</b>

119
00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:16.980
That's meowt of the question!

120
00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:19.980
Mew might as well just
destroy the whole town!

121
00:08:24.610 --> 00:08:25.690
I found him!

122
00:08:31.490 --> 00:08:33.700
Damn! I guess I can't outrun them!

123
00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:37.160
Somehow...

124
00:08:38.210 --> 00:08:43.500
I have to keep them busy until
everyone can escape to the sea!

125
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:47.880
Koby the Hero!

126
00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:56.640
Koby the Hero, I want to turn this island...

127
00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:00.940
this Pirate Island...

128
00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:05.150
into a full-fledged nation!

129
00:09:05.150 --> 00:09:09.360
A World Government-affiliated nation!

130
00:09:10.610 --> 00:09:12.320
It'll be the Blackbeard Kingdom...

131
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:14.700
with me as its king!

132
00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.120
How's that?

133
00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.210
Stop this nonsense.

134
00:09:22.580 --> 00:09:24.710
There's no way it would work!

135
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:27.170
It'd be a country of criminals!

136
00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:31.550
Hey, don't step on a man's dream!

137
00:09:31.550 --> 00:09:35.550
I'll negotiate with them
using you as a bargaining chip.

138
00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:40.600
If the government or the Marines
give in to terrorists, we're all doomed!

139
00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:43.940
Anyway, you're wasting your time.

140
00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:45.860
Because...

141
00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:48.530
I'm a member of SWORD!

142
00:09:49.780 --> 00:09:51.610
SWORD?

143
00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:53.320
What the hell is that?

144
00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:54.870
Oh, I see...

145
00:09:54.870 --> 00:09:55.570
Huh?

146
00:09:55.570 --> 00:09:57.580
This isn't gonna go well.

147
00:09:57.580 --> 00:09:59.910
Give up on the trade, Teach.

148
00:10:07.590 --> 00:10:09.130
What he means...

149
00:10:09.130 --> 00:10:12.170
is that he's a Marine but also not.

150
00:10:13.470 --> 00:10:15.930
He gave up his Marine code.

151
00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:22.690
SWORD is a group of Marines that have
already submitted their resignations.

152
00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:27.270
Which means they could even fight
the Four Emperors without permission.

153
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:31.610
They can operate however they choose
and disregard any and all orders.

154
00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:32.820
They're free agents.

155
00:10:33.320 --> 00:10:34.820
In exchange...

156
00:10:36.030 --> 00:10:39.870
the Marines are in no way
responsible for their actions...

157
00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:42.620
and can fire them anytime.

158
00:10:45.210 --> 00:10:46.580
I see!

159
00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:50.840
So there's the normal idiots who
sit around waiting for permission,

160
00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:54.680
and you guys, who charge in
without thinking twice!

161
00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:59.810
Now that I get it, I like your style!

162
00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:02.140
But...

163
00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:04.770
I'm not gonna change the plan!

164
00:11:05.350 --> 00:11:07.150
I'll do it anyway!

165
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:10.570
Even if you're in SWORD,

166
00:11:11.280 --> 00:11:14.820
the people still call you a hero.

167
00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:18.240
I wonder if the Marines can
really afford to just abandon you.

168
00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:21.490
Let's ask the public, shall we?!

169
00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:25.660
That way the government can't just
wash their hands of this!

170
00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:31.750
Until then, lock him up!

171
00:11:33.170 --> 00:11:35.010
I can't wait!

172
00:11:35.010 --> 00:11:37.720
Don't let him escape!

173
00:11:39.470 --> 00:11:42.310
Get back here, Koby!

174
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:49.360
Hey!

175
00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:55.650
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

176
00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:58.450
I may have cooperated with a pirate...

177
00:11:58.950 --> 00:12:01.330
but you gotta do what you gotta do!

178
00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:09.790
What's that?

179
00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:22.180
Three Marines spotted at the port!

180
00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:25.220
What? Marines?! No way!

181
00:12:25.850 --> 00:12:27.180
Hurry up!

182
00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.810
They're strong! Be careful!

183
00:12:32.610 --> 00:12:34.730
Did someone come to rescue me?

184
00:12:34.730 --> 00:12:36.070
No, no!

185
00:12:36.070 --> 00:12:37.740
How arrogant of me!

186
00:12:37.740 --> 00:12:38.950
I'm ashamed!

187
00:12:58.630 --> 00:12:59.760
Who are they?!

188
00:12:59.760 --> 00:13:01.260
Why are they so strong?!

189
00:13:01.260 --> 00:13:03.760
They're heading toward
the center of the town!

190
00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:04.720
What do they want?!

191
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:07.140
Who cares?! Stop them!

192
00:13:14.730 --> 00:13:15.730
What?

193
00:13:15.730 --> 00:13:17.190
Guns don't work on them!

194
00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:20.990
That's as far as you go!

195
00:13:24.410 --> 00:13:25.990
He cut his head off!

196
00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:32.210
I took one down!

197
00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:33.920
That'll teach you!

198
00:13:40.510 --> 00:13:41.800
That hurt...

199
00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:42.800
What?!

200
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:43.930
A logia?!

201
00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:45.800
What's with this guy?!

202
00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:48.100
It's like he's made of clay!

203
00:13:49.640 --> 00:13:52.020
Where are you, Koby?!

204
00:13:54.230 --> 00:13:55.980
H-Hey...

205
00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:58.730
Are those buildings moving?!

206
00:13:58.730 --> 00:14:00.490
No, stupid! Of course not!

207
00:14:00.490 --> 00:14:02.450
You drink too much!

208
00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.250
Go on! Be a good little boy!

209
00:14:15.380 --> 00:14:17.130
Get a move on!

210
00:14:17.130 --> 00:14:20.090
What a weird lady. Who is that?

211
00:14:20.090 --> 00:14:22.880
Come on, straighten up!

212
00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:27.510
You look pathetic!

213
00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:29.640
Come on! Come on! Come on!

214
00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:32.140
She's whipping a building...

215
00:14:33.350 --> 00:14:35.560
What is it? Staring, are we?

216
00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:37.270
What? No, I...

217
00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:39.980
S-She's a Marine?!

218
00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:50.410
Is it that rare for a pirate
to set eyes on a Marine?

219
00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:53.410
<b>Rear Admiral Kujaku
Marine Headquarters (SWORD)
Granddaughter of "Master Tactician" Tsuru
Whip-Whip Fruit
Discipline Woman</b>

220
00:14:53.410 --> 00:14:55.670
Come to me.

221
00:14:55.670 --> 00:14:57.170
You're so cute.

222
00:15:04.760 --> 00:15:06.640
I'll whip you into shape.

223
00:15:14.020 --> 00:15:16.100
You're cornered, Koby!

224
00:15:16.480 --> 00:15:18.610
Oh no! I'm surrounded!

225
00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:25.280
Take aim!

226
00:15:27.530 --> 00:15:28.490
Is this it for me?

227
00:15:28.990 --> 00:15:30.700
On my mark!

228
00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.290
Fire!

229
00:15:45.010 --> 00:15:45.590
What?!

230
00:15:46.090 --> 00:15:47.130
What?

231
00:15:48.390 --> 00:15:50.100
What?

232
00:15:53.350 --> 00:15:55.520
What? What?

233
00:15:56.440 --> 00:15:57.810
What?!

234
00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:02.980
It's beautiful!

235
00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:04.070
Wait, no!

236
00:16:04.070 --> 00:16:05.440
What the hell is this?!

237
00:16:05.860 --> 00:16:08.200
Why did a flower come out of the muzzle?!

238
00:16:09.450 --> 00:16:11.700
No, wait...

239
00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:12.870
This is...

240
00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:18.170
one of Dr. Vegapunk's inventions!

241
00:16:22.590 --> 00:16:25.710
It earned him the Mobel Peace Prize!

242
00:16:26.760 --> 00:16:28.840
That's not what I'm asking!

243
00:16:29.470 --> 00:16:31.800
Who did this?!

244
00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:33.010
Koby!

245
00:16:36.430 --> 00:16:38.440
Get over here!

246
00:16:38.440 --> 00:16:39.140
Wait, no!

247
00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:41.360
I didn't mean anythin' weird!

248
00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:45.320
<b>Commander Hibari
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)</b>

249
00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:48.110
Hibari! What are you doing here?!

250
00:16:48.650 --> 00:16:49.740
Don't tell me...

251
00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:50.860
Yes!

252
00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:54.450
I shot them with flower rounds,
which cause gunpowder to bloom!

253
00:16:54.790 --> 00:16:56.950
They can't use their weapons!

254
00:16:56.950 --> 00:16:58.910
Run while you can!

255
00:16:59.370 --> 00:17:01.790
A-And...

256
00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:03.630
if you're hungry, I...

257
00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:05.250
made...

258
00:17:06.630 --> 00:17:08.010
lunch for you!

259
00:17:08.010 --> 00:17:09.090
Huh?

260
00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:11.590
No, I mean...

261
00:17:19.180 --> 00:17:20.560
Prince! Any progress?

262
00:17:21.810 --> 00:17:24.770
Yeah, we just finished up here.

263
00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:32.200
<b>Rear Admiral Prince Grus</b>
<b>Marine Headquarters</b>

264
00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:34.660
<b>Glorp-Glorp Fruit</b>
<b>Clay Man</b>

265
00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:34.070
Koby is safe, too!

266
00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:37.120
<b>Mud Puppet (Golem)</b>

267
00:17:37.490 --> 00:17:40.960
H-Hey... Has this square
always been shaped like this?

268
00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:41.580
What?

269
00:17:44.290 --> 00:17:47.300
Isn't that building moving?

270
00:17:47.300 --> 00:17:48.760
H-Hey, wait!

271
00:17:52.090 --> 00:17:53.800
O-Oh no...

272
00:17:53.800 --> 00:17:55.890
We can't get out of here!

273
00:17:55.890 --> 00:17:57.890
Now, whenever you're ready!

274
00:17:58.270 --> 00:17:59.850
Head to the very center!

275
00:18:00.230 --> 00:18:02.190
I was able to contact Prince!

276
00:18:02.520 --> 00:18:03.940
It's all ready!

277
00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:05.440
Vice Admiral Garp!

278
00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:09.440
Everyone, hang onto something!

279
00:18:12.030 --> 00:18:14.320
Charge!

280
00:18:22.620 --> 00:18:23.960
C'mon! Hurry up!

281
00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:26.210
Let's get out of here!

282
00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:33.470
Look up!

283
00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:40.220
Whaaat?!

284
00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:46.980
– Whaaat?!
– Whaaat?!

285
00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:51.320
A Marine ship is flying through the sky!

286
00:18:51.320 --> 00:18:53.990
Why?! How is that possible?!

287
00:18:53.990 --> 00:18:55.320
Who's on it?!

288
00:18:56.780 --> 00:18:59.700
Isn't it... falling toward us?

289
00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:02.250
R-Run!

290
00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:07.080
Look!

291
00:19:07.080 --> 00:19:08.590
On the ship!

292
00:19:11.380 --> 00:19:14.840
No way! I thought he retired!

293
00:19:15.340 --> 00:19:16.800
The legendary...

294
00:19:16.800 --> 00:19:18.390
Hero!

295
00:19:23.520 --> 00:19:26.480
Vice Admiral Garp!

296
00:19:26.980 --> 00:19:28.480
Koby!

297
00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:30.480
I'm here to save you!

298
00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:34.990
Run! Just run!

299
00:19:34.990 --> 00:19:35.950
We can't...

300
00:19:35.950 --> 00:19:37.910
There's no way out!

301
00:19:41.490 --> 00:19:45.040
Hey, you damn pirates!

302
00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:48.000
He's coming! Run!

303
00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:08.770
Vice Admiral Garp...

304
00:20:09.810 --> 00:20:12.900
Why? I'm not even worth saving...

305
00:20:13.320 --> 00:20:14.900
You idiots!

306
00:20:15.610 --> 00:20:20.870
Do you have any idea who
the hell you've kidnapped?!

307
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:32.170
Koby is the future of the Marines!

308
00:20:33.340 --> 00:20:35.960
Not to mention...

309
00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:40.550
my precious protégé!

310
00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:45.220
Galaxy...

311
00:20:56.400 --> 00:21:00.280
Impact!

312
00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:01.630
Cumulo-glorpus!

313
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:16.610
Damn you, Garp!

314
00:22:16.610 --> 00:22:18.190
He's insane!

315
00:22:18.190 --> 00:22:20.440
I'll make that geezer pay!

316
00:22:20.440 --> 00:22:22.150
Don't move, pirates!

317
00:22:23.110 --> 00:22:26.870
Resistance will only result in further damage!

318
00:22:33.870 --> 00:22:36.380
Absolutely pathetic...

319
00:22:37.170 --> 00:22:39.170
I've really gotten rusty.

320
00:22:39.800 --> 00:22:41.170
Screw you!

321
00:22:41.170 --> 00:22:43.800
As if there's anything left to damage!

322
00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:46.140
Vice Admiral Garp!

323
00:22:47.930 --> 00:22:49.470
Oh, Koby!

324
00:22:50.140 --> 00:22:51.890
You're okay!

325
00:22:54.140 --> 00:22:56.020
Thank goodness!

326
00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:58.400
They didn't kill him!

327
00:22:58.400 --> 00:23:00.030
Really now...

328
00:23:00.030 --> 00:23:01.530
He overdid it.

329
00:23:01.530 --> 00:23:04.400
You're such a naughty boy, Garp!

330
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:08.370
Garp said Koby's the future of
the Marines. I won't stand for it!

331
00:23:08.370 --> 00:23:10.580
I'm gonna sabotage him!

332
00:23:10.580 --> 00:23:15.080
That's something you're supposed
to keep to yourself, you spoiled brat.

333
00:23:15.080 --> 00:23:16.710
It's cuter that way.

334
00:23:16.710 --> 00:23:18.790
Koby!

335
00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:21.090
Captain Koby!

336
00:23:21.420 --> 00:23:23.550
Koby!

337
00:23:23.550 --> 00:23:25.260
Tashigi!

338
00:23:25.630 --> 00:23:28.010
Even non-SWORD members came...

339
00:23:29.140 --> 00:23:32.100
Hey, Koby! Why are you
lugging that thing around?

340
00:23:32.100 --> 00:23:33.430
Vice Admiral Garp!

341
00:23:33.850 --> 00:23:37.520
We've tried everything,
but we can't get the shackle off!!

342
00:23:37.520 --> 00:23:38.480
Please...

343
00:23:40.860 --> 00:23:42.190
do...

344
00:23:42.780 --> 00:23:44.030
some...

345
00:23:45.150 --> 00:23:46.780
thing...

346
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:52.080
Hibari...!

347
00:23:52.080 --> 00:23:53.290
Hibari!

348
00:23:56.670 --> 00:23:57.960
Hibari!

349
00:24:10.010 --> 00:24:11.260
Kuzan.

350
00:24:11.760 --> 00:24:13.220
Kuzan!

351
00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:14.980
What are you doing?!

352
00:24:14.980 --> 00:24:17.480
Please thaw her out right now!

353
00:24:19.060 --> 00:24:21.060
It's Aokiji!

354
00:24:21.690 --> 00:24:24.190
Captain Kuzan!

355
00:24:24.190 --> 00:24:26.030
Kuzan!

356
00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:29.280
Don't get me in trouble, Koby.

357
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.200
I can't have you running off...

358
00:24:31.620 --> 00:24:34.330
while Teach is away.

359
00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:40.830
Two years ago, Admiral Akainu and Admiral Aokiji...

360
00:24:41.420 --> 00:24:47.510
fought for the position of the next
fleet admiral of Marine Headquarters.

361
00:24:51.640 --> 00:24:56.020
The deadly struggle went on for
ten days before a victor emerged:

362
00:24:56.680 --> 00:24:57.730
Akainu.

363
00:24:59.440 --> 00:25:04.020
However, Aokiji refused to serve under him.

364
00:25:04.400 --> 00:25:06.400
And so, he left the Marines.

365
00:25:12.530 --> 00:25:17.500
<b>Some Island, New World</b>

366
00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:28.380
What the...?!

367
00:25:28.720 --> 00:25:30.510
Blackbeard's here!

368
00:25:30.510 --> 00:25:33.300
Run! Get out of the town!

369
00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:34.220
Hey!

370
00:25:34.220 --> 00:25:36.430
What happened here?

371
00:25:36.430 --> 00:25:39.390
Wait! Who did this?!

372
00:25:43.520 --> 00:25:45.980
No, I don't need to ask...

373
00:25:47.320 --> 00:25:52.740
There's only one person
in the world who could've done this!

374
00:25:54.700 --> 00:25:56.160
It's you!

375
00:25:56.160 --> 00:25:58.200
Aokiji!

376
00:26:10.800 --> 00:26:13.430
My crew is frozen solid outside!

377
00:26:13.430 --> 00:26:15.850
Undo it!

378
00:26:16.720 --> 00:26:19.310
You're annoying me.

379
00:26:20.310 --> 00:26:22.940
And don't even think about using your power.

380
00:26:24.440 --> 00:26:26.730
Your crew will shatter and die.

381
00:26:28.230 --> 00:26:31.490
You're their captain, so I think you know.

382
00:26:32.740 --> 00:26:35.200
Do you really think I started it?

383
00:26:35.950 --> 00:26:38.910
Besides, you already know, don't you?

384
00:26:39.660 --> 00:26:43.830
I'm not just heartbroken, I'm furious.

385
00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:48.800
Take a guess who actually started this.

386
00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:15.070
Another round over here!

387
00:27:16.780 --> 00:27:19.870
You can really knock 'em back, Ice Pop!

388
00:27:19.870 --> 00:27:22.620
You're not bad yourself, you son of a bitch!

389
00:27:25.080 --> 00:27:28.210
So what did Akainu say next?

390
00:27:31.840 --> 00:27:34.970
"Two men who enlisted the same year
in a fight to the death...

391
00:27:34.970 --> 00:27:38.180
My eyes are burning with tears."

392
00:27:38.890 --> 00:27:41.890
And I said, "Yeah, that's 'cause...

393
00:27:42.220 --> 00:27:44.930
your magma's flowing!"

394
00:27:47.100 --> 00:27:48.610
And now look at me!

395
00:27:52.530 --> 00:27:54.490
I'm down to one leg!

396
00:27:55.400 --> 00:27:58.360
So that's what happens
when two admirals fight!

397
00:27:58.360 --> 00:27:59.910
What about Akainu?

398
00:28:00.450 --> 00:28:02.830
Did you at least rip one of his arms off?!

399
00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:04.200
No...

400
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:09.540
But I'm sure he's scarred to all hell.

401
00:28:12.130 --> 00:28:16.470
Speaking of scars, he might know
Burn Scar, Commodore.

402
00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:18.970
Huh? Burn Scar?

403
00:28:18.970 --> 00:28:24.770
There are four important
red lode poneglyphs in the world.

404
00:28:26.890 --> 00:28:31.560
Big Mom and Kaido have two of them...

405
00:28:33.190 --> 00:28:37.530
But we can't find the other two!

406
00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:40.280
Once more fate rears its head...

407
00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:41.240
Yeah...

408
00:28:41.240 --> 00:28:47.250
And they say that the Man with
the Burn Scar has one of them.

409
00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:50.120
Is it me?

410
00:28:50.120 --> 00:28:52.500
You just got that scar, you idiot!

411
00:28:57.170 --> 00:28:59.180
Rumor has it...

412
00:29:05.470 --> 00:29:10.310
that he sails a pitch-black ship.

413
00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:22.990
And when you get close, he creates
a giant whirlpool to swallow you up.

414
00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:30.500
He may have eaten a devil fruit...

415
00:29:31.120 --> 00:29:34.710
I believe he works for the government.

416
00:29:35.210 --> 00:29:38.760
The World Government has
dark secrets, after all.

417
00:29:38.760 --> 00:29:41.630
If they hold on to even one of the stones,

418
00:29:41.630 --> 00:29:50.180
it means that no pirate will ever reach the
One Piece, the single greatest hidden treasure.

419
00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:55.570
The poneglyphs... I only have
bitter memories involving them.

420
00:29:55.570 --> 00:30:01.240
If I saw a red stone like that
in Ohara, I'd remember it.

421
00:30:02.860 --> 00:30:04.990
All I can remember...

422
00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:08.240
is a good friend who rebelled
against the government...

423
00:30:08.240 --> 00:30:11.080
and a girl with eyes full of despair...

424
00:30:11.580 --> 00:30:15.340
whose fate was in my hands.

425
00:30:17.670 --> 00:30:20.550
What kind of boring story is that?!

426
00:30:23.380 --> 00:30:25.600
Commodore, what should we do?

427
00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:26.220
Huh?

428
00:30:26.600 --> 00:30:30.930
If we take his power for ourselves,
it'll be a considerable asset to us...

429
00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:39.360
I heard that, you slimy bastards!

430
00:30:41.570 --> 00:30:45.530
How about I send you to an icy hell?!

431
00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.450
Stop, stop, stop!

432
00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:57.790
That's right, I've already heard about
you guys hunting devil fruit powers.

433
00:30:59.210 --> 00:31:00.960
Bring it on!

434
00:31:06.590 --> 00:31:07.800
Wait!

435
00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.930
I'm sorry!

436
00:31:09.930 --> 00:31:12.680
What my crew member said was ridiculous.

437
00:31:13.310 --> 00:31:15.850
I wouldn't dream of doing that.

438
00:31:15.850 --> 00:31:17.980
What I really wanted to ask you was...

439
00:31:17.980 --> 00:31:20.440
Do you wanna sail with us?

440
00:31:21.400 --> 00:31:24.650
What?! Captain, are you off your rocker?!

441
00:31:24.650 --> 00:31:27.620
You lost your position, didn't you?

442
00:31:27.620 --> 00:31:29.620
Do you have a place to go?

443
00:31:29.620 --> 00:31:31.620
What are you gonna do now?

444
00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:34.040
The guardians of justice have abandoned you!

445
00:31:35.080 --> 00:31:37.210
Man, this must be rock bottom.

446
00:31:37.210 --> 00:31:41.090
A pirate worrying about my prospects.

447
00:31:41.090 --> 00:31:44.300
Wherever you go, whatever you do,

448
00:31:44.920 --> 00:31:48.050
trouble will always find you!

449
00:31:48.050 --> 00:31:53.220
So what flag are you gonna fight under?

450
00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:54.640
Huh?!

451
00:31:56.020 --> 00:31:59.020
I'm different from the Marines!

452
00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:01.860
I have my own brand of justice!

453
00:32:01.860 --> 00:32:03.190
Don't be stupid!

454
00:32:03.190 --> 00:32:08.200
Just because we shared a few drinks
doesn't mean I trust scum like you!

455
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:09.570
Whoa, whoa!

456
00:32:09.570 --> 00:32:12.450
I think you have the wrong idea about pirates.

457
00:32:12.450 --> 00:32:16.460
It's not like we're all buddies here!

458
00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:23.840
The only thing a pirate crew needs...

459
00:32:26.510 --> 00:32:30.680
is to have mutual interests!

460
00:32:33.560 --> 00:32:36.680
You're free now...

461
00:32:38.190 --> 00:32:40.100
so what do you wanna do?

462
00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:56.290
Hey, Kuzan!

463
00:32:56.750 --> 00:32:58.580
Thaw out Hibari!

464
00:32:59.120 --> 00:33:00.920
Let Koby escape!

465
00:33:00.920 --> 00:33:03.630
Come back to the Marines!

466
00:33:06.380 --> 00:33:11.510
You haven't changed at all.
Always saying what's on your mind.

467
00:33:15.220 --> 00:33:19.310
But I can't let any of that happen, Garp!

468
00:33:20.230 --> 00:33:22.020
I've always loved...

469
00:33:22.900 --> 00:33:24.730
how straightforward you are...

470
00:33:25.360 --> 00:33:29.650
which is why I'm living the way I want to now!

471
00:33:26.650 --> 00:33:29.650
<b>Kuzan
Captain of the Tenth Ship
Blackbeard Pirates</b>

472
00:33:34.870 --> 00:33:36.240
Bonehead...

473
00:33:52.970 --> 00:33:53.800
Ice...

474
00:33:54.300 --> 00:33:55.510
Ball!

475
00:34:01.770 --> 00:34:03.730
Vice Admiral Garp!

476
00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:07.730
Vice Admiral Garp!

477
00:34:11.200 --> 00:34:13.820
In order to save your beloved protégé,

478
00:34:14.410 --> 00:34:18.910
can you kill your former star pupil?!

479
00:34:20.620 --> 00:34:22.830
Don't live in the past, you moron!

480
00:34:24.460 --> 00:34:27.710
I taught you to live in the moment!

481
00:34:33.090 --> 00:34:34.180
It didn't work!

482
00:34:54.410 --> 00:34:56.160
Listen, Kuzan!

483
00:35:19.350 --> 00:35:21.560
Wavering is a sign...

484
00:35:23.310 --> 00:35:24.270
of weakness!

485
00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:29.900
Blue Hole!

486
00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:04.060
<b>Winner Island
New World</b>

487
00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:02.600
Meanwhile, at Winner Island...

488
00:36:39.390 --> 00:36:44.270
You can hardly call yourself
a pirate crew without a ship!

489
00:36:44.770 --> 00:36:47.480
There's no way for you to escape!

490
00:36:48.100 --> 00:36:54.360
The hundred pirates whose hearts
you stole at Rocky Port...

491
00:36:54.360 --> 00:36:58.950
are still living in fear on the Pirate Island!

492
00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:05.540
But if I bring them your heart,
they're sure to raise a toast!

493
00:37:12.420 --> 00:37:14.670
You really made it for me!

494
00:37:14.670 --> 00:37:18.630
But I can't guarantee it'll work.

495
00:37:24.390 --> 00:37:26.020
Now...

496
00:37:26.020 --> 00:37:30.390
I'm having a hard time deciding whether
to sell or use the Op-Op Fruit.

497
00:37:30.390 --> 00:37:33.610
It can even grant me eternal youth, can't it?!

498
00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:44.120
Get your hands...

499
00:37:46.240 --> 00:37:48.000
off my captain!

500
00:37:57.710 --> 00:37:58.880
Bepo...

501
00:38:04.720 --> 00:38:06.850
What?! Sulong?!

502
00:38:06.850 --> 00:38:09.310
No way! The moon isn't even out!

503
00:38:18.860 --> 00:38:20.860
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

504
00:38:37.170 --> 00:38:38.210
Captain!

505
00:39:00.030 --> 00:39:02.320
Dammit! They fled to sea!

506
00:39:02.320 --> 00:39:04.530
Don't let him get away!

507
00:39:11.500 --> 00:39:14.080
Go back, Bepo...

508
00:39:18.540 --> 00:39:22.840
I can't... leave the crew... behind...

509
00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:24.590
I won't go back!

510
00:39:25.340 --> 00:39:27.720
Trust them, Captain!

511
00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:30.510
From that frigid northern port
all the way until now...

512
00:39:32.520 --> 00:39:35.900
we've always survived!

513
00:39:35.900 --> 00:39:37.190
So...

514
00:39:38.480 --> 00:39:40.980
none of us will die here!

515
00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:49.490
We've overcome so much together!

516
00:39:51.580 --> 00:39:53.450
So, Captain!

517
00:39:54.540 --> 00:39:57.120
Don't die!

518
00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:07.470
Please...

519
00:40:08.840 --> 00:40:10.850
don't die!

520
00:40:16.060 --> 00:40:19.770
At Winner Island in the New World...

521
00:40:28.320 --> 00:40:33.040
the Heart Pirates' submarine, the Polar Tang,

522
00:40:33.410 --> 00:40:34.910
was sunk.

523
00:40:38.370 --> 00:40:42.540
The Heart Pirates led by Trafalgar Law...

524
00:40:43.750 --> 00:40:45.260
were defeated.

525
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:59.300
Running so long lost track of just how long its been

526
00:41:00.150 --> 00:41:06.660
Collected scars while striving not even trying beneath my skin

527
00:41:07.160 --> 00:41:14.080
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead I remember a map

528
00:41:14.160 --> 00:41:20.370
to a treasure still gleaming its within our grasp

529
00:41:20.510 --> 00:41:27.280
Can you feel my heart Feelings I impart

530
00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:34.390
The promises are there theyre deep down but still primed to share

531
00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:43.500
Peerless dreams kept close the dreams that always matter most

532
00:41:43.680 --> 00:41:49.250
Before we set sail why not raise a toast

533
00:41:49.370 --> 00:41:56.280
So I pen this note to you Dear sunrise Ill see you soon

534
00:41:56.440 --> 00:42:03.470
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

535
00:42:03.450 --> 00:42:10.520
And regardless of our age these memries will still remain

536
00:42:10.420 --> 00:42:17.630
Wont forget until this wish makes it to you
